<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 4:18PM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Union
County through 445 PM CDT...
At 417 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wesson, or 8 miles northwest of Junction City, moving southwest at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wesson, Three Creeks and Hew Hope.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
